The `Wrapping/Neighbourhood` classes in `math/Topology` share huge amount of code, and would benefit from:

- [ ] extend from a common ancestor (Neighbourhood)
- [ ] remove the duplicit code
- [ ] optimize its use in SP *) see below

In SP, we often see a suboptimal situation with an `if` inside a `for` loop, like this:
```
void blah(){
  if (wrapAround_)
    for (v : Neighbourhood)
        ...
  else
    for(v : WrappingNeigh)
      ...
```

We can store a reference to the desired class during init:
```
Neighbourhood hood;
if(wrapAround_)
  hood = WrappingNeighbourhood;
else
  hood = Neigh...
```
and then simplify all the `for`s.

