Personally I need the current user a lot so have added these mixins myself anyway. Thought it might be a nice addition for others. Make sure to add them as the first in the class.

```
class UserDTKwargsMixin(object):
    def get_datatable_kwargs(self, **kwargs):
        kwargs = super(UserDTKwargsMixin, self).get_datatable_kwargs(**kwargs)
        kwargs.update({"user": self.request.user})
        return kwargs


class UserKwargModelDTMixin(object):
    def __init__(self, object_list, url, view=None, callback_target=None, model=None, query_config=None,
                 force_distinct=True, **kwargs):
        self.user = kwargs.pop("user", None)
        super(UserKwargModelDTMixin, self).__init__(object_list, url, view, callback_target, model, query_config,
                                                    force_distinct, **kwargs)
```

Usage:

```
class Table(UserKwargModelDTMixin, Datatable):

class View(UserDTKwargsMixin, DatatableView):
```

